<item>
            <title>[SPARK-9973] Wrong initial size of in-memory columnar buffers</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-9973</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Two much memory is allocated for in-memory columnar buffers. The &lt;tt&gt;initialSize&lt;/tt&gt; argument in &lt;tt&gt;ColumnBuilder.initialize&lt;/tt&gt; is the initial number of rows rather than bytes, but the value passed in in &lt;tt&gt;InMemoryColumnarTableScan&lt;/tt&gt; is the latter:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Class&lt;/span&gt; InMemoryColumnarTableScan
&lt;/span&gt;  val initialBufferSize = columnType.defaultSize * batchSize
  ColumnBuilder(attribute.dataType, initialBufferSize, attribute.name, useCompression)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then it&apos;s converted to byte size again by multiplying &lt;tt&gt;columnType.defaultSize&lt;/tt&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Class&lt;/span&gt; BasicColumnBuilder
&lt;/span&gt;  buffer = ByteBuffer.allocate(4 + size * columnType.defaultSize)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
